using UnityEngine;

public class GenericError
{
    // Forgetting to specify type parameter
    public T FindMax<T>(T a, T b) where T : System.IComparable<T>
    {
        return a.CompareTo(b) > 0 ? a : b;
    }

    void Start()
    {
        // Trying to use the method without specifying type
        int result = FindMax(10, 20);  // Error!
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
The compiler can't infer the type because you're using it incorrectly.

**The fix:**
```csharp
int result = FindMax<int>(10, 20);  // Specify the type
```

**Or make it static:**
```csharp
public static T FindMax<T>(T a, T b) where T : System.IComparable<T>
{
    return a.CompareTo(b) > 0 ? a : b;
}

// Usage
int result = Utility.FindMax(10, 20);
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Generic methods need type inference or explicit type arguments."
